[30;1m130 | [0m[35mor if there are clock changes for daylight saving in your zone), you can have some problems [0m
[30;1m131 | [0m[35mwith update commands that depend from file's modification time. It's strongly recommended to use onl[0m
[30;1m132 | [0m[35mfile system that uses Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) and archive format that also uses UTC. [0m

[30;1m507 | [0m[35m     of this as transportation from the present into the future.  (It is[0m
[30;1m508 | [0m[35m     a science-fiction idiom that you can move through time as well as[0m
[30;1m509 | [0m[35m     in space; the idea here is that 'tar' can be used to move archives[0m
[30;1m510 | [0m[35m     in all dimensions, even time!)[0m

[30;1m499 | [0m[35m     tape has no names for these files; it only knows their relative[0m
[30;1m500 | [0m[35m     position on the tape.  One way to store several files on one tape[0m
[30;1m501 | [0m[35m     and retain their names is by creating a 'tar' archive.  Even when[0m
[30;1m502 | [0m[35m     the basic transfer mechanism can keep track of names, as FTP can,[0m
[30;1m503 | [0m[35m     the nuisance of handling multiple files, directories, and multiple[0m
[30;1m504 | [0m[35m     links makes 'tar' archives useful.[0m
[30;1m505 | [0m[35m[0m
